{"ts":"2026-06-27T22:59:26.888Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"qhmdqzyc","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/PHASE_6_AWS_FINAL_SETUP.md:50-180","result":" 50 | *   **Purpose**: Single-table design housing the 6 core operational models of the GFF AI Portal.\n 51 | \n 52 | #### Entity Mappings & Storage Patterns\n 53 | \n 54 | 1. **Projects**\n 55 |    - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>`\n 56 |    - **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `METADATA`\n 57 |    - **Attributes**: `name`, `status`, `progress`, `budget`, `created_at`\n 58 | \n 59 | 2. **AI Operations**\n 60 |    - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `AIOPS#<ops_id>`\n 61 |    - **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` (links to project) | **`GSI1SK`**: `AIOPS#<ops_id>`\n 62 |    - **Attributes**: `name`, `status`, `agent_count`, `runtime_seconds`, `cpu_usage`, `memory_usage`\n 63 | \n 64 | 3. **Documents Metadata**\n 65 |    - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `DOC#<doc_id>`\n 66 |    - **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` (retrieves files by project) | **`GSI1SK`**: `DOC#<doc_id>`\n 67 |    - **Attributes**: `title`, `s3_key`, `file_size`, `category`, `uploaded_by`, `uploaded_at`\n 68 | \n 69 | 4. **Invoices Metadata**\n 70 |    - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `INV#<invoice_id>`\n 71 |    - **`GSI1PK`**: `BILLING_PERIOD#<year_month>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `INV#<invoice_id>`\n 72 |    - **Attributes**: `amount_usd`, `status`, `due_date`, `epochs_consumed`, `created_at`\n 73 | \n 74 | 5. **Support Tickets**\n 75 |    - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `TICKET#<ticket_id>`\n 76 |    - **`GSI1PK`**: `STATUS#<status_code>` (supports dashboard queues) | **`GSI1SK`**: `TICKET#<ticket_id>`\n 77 |    - **Attributes**: `subject`, `priority`, `status_text`, `assigned_to`, `created_at`\n 78 | \n 79 | 6. **Governance Items**\n 80 |    - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `GOV#<gov_id>`\n 81 |    - **`GSI1PK`**: `STANDARD#<compliance_standard>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `GOV#<gov_id>`\n 82 |    - **Attributes**: `control_name`, `status`, `remediation_notes`, `assessed_at`\n 83 | \n 84 | ---\n 85 | \n 86 | ## 3. Cloud Object Storage Setup (Amazon S3)\n 87 | \n 88 | *   **Bucket Reference**: `gff-portal-documents-prod`\n 89 | *   **Security Configurations**:\n 90 |     *   **Block Public Access**: Enabled.\n 91 |     *   **Encryption at Rest**: Enforced using KMS customer-managed keys (SSE-KMS).\n 92 |     *   **Secure Transport**: Restricts transport to TLS 1.3/HTTPS.\n 93 |     *   **Presigned Access**: Frontend uploads/downloads via short-lived pre-signed URLs generated by Lambda (valid for 15 minutes).\n 94 | \n 95 | ---\n 96 | \n 97 | ## 4. Required Deployment Environment Keys\n 98 | \n 99 | ### 4.1. Next.js Frontend Keys (`.env.production`)\n100 | ```env\n101 | NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://api.gff.ai/v1\n102 | NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV=production\n103 | NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_UPLOADS_ENABLED=true\n104 | NEXT_PUBLIC_S3_BUCKET_NAME=gff-portal-documents-prod\n105 | ```\n106 | \n107 | ### 4.2. FastAPI AWS Backend Keys (`backend/prod.env` / Lambda Variables)\n108 | ```env\n109 | PROJECT_NAME=\"GFF AI Enterprise Cloud Engine\"\n110 | API_V1_STR=\"/api/v1\"\n111 | ENVIRONMENT=\"production\"\n112 | CORS_ORIGINS=\"https://portal.gff.ai,https://admin.gff.ai\"\n113 | FRONTEND_BASE_URL=\"https://portal.gff.ai\"\n114 | AWS_REGION=us-east-1\n115 | AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=production_aws_access_key_id\n116 | AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=production_aws_secret_access_key\n117 | DYNAMODB_USERS_TABLE=GFF_USERS\n118 | DYNAMODB_CLIENTS_TABLE=GFF_CLIENTS\n119 | DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TABLE=GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS\n120 | DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TYPE_INDEX=GSI1\n121 | S3_DOCUMENTS_BUCKET=gff-portal-documents-prod\n122 | S3_DOCUMENTS_PREFIX=clients\n123 | JWT_SECRET=production_cryptographically_secure_256_bit_signature_key_2026\n124 | ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=1440\n125 | ```\n126 | \n127 | \n128 | ---\n129 | \n130 | ## 5. Seeded User Credentials (Final MVP Data)\n131 | \n132 | The system contains exactly **four** seeded user accounts covering the three standard RBAC roles (`gff_admin`, `client_admin`, `client_member`). All passwords, roles, and client associations are modeled to enable immediate high-fidelity secure testing.\n133 | \n134 | | Role | Email | Password | Associated Client | Notes |\n135 | | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n136 | | **`gff_admin`** | `gff_admin@gff.ai` | `password123` | *None* | Global platform administrator. Accesses the GFF Admin Panel. |\n137 | | **`client_admin`** | `client_admin@apex.com` | `password123` | `Apex Global Solutions` (ID: 1) | Enterprise client administrator. Full workspace management for Client 1. |\n138 | | **`client_member`** | `client_member@apex.com` | `password123` | `Apex Global Solutions` (ID: 1) | Client 1 standard user. Limited operational access inside Client 1 workspace. |\n139 | | **`client_member`** | `client@chevron.com` | `chevron_secure_pass_2026` | `Sovereign Logistics Corp` (ID: 2) | Client 2 standard user. Used to verify cross-tenant security and upload/download boundaries in smoke tests. |\n140 | \n141 | These credentials can be used both locally (via SQLite/mock fallbacks) and in the production cloud (AWS DynamoDB) once the environment is initialized and seeded using:\n142 | ```bash\n143 | npm run backend:seed\n144 | ```\n145 | \n146 | \n147 | \n148 | ---\n149 | \n150 | ## 6. Execution, Build, and Deployment Manual\n151 | \n152 | This section outlines the operational commands, deployment procedures, required environment parameters, and AWS production resources for launching the GFF AI Platform.\n153 | \n154 | ### 6.1. Backend Execution & Deployment Commands\n155 | \n156 | The backend is built as a cloud-ready FastAPI application that can be run locally using Uvicorn or deployed to AWS Lambda (e.g., using Mangum adapter) or AWS App Runner / Elastic Beanstalk.\n157 | \n158 | #### 1. Setup & Installation\n159 | To create the virtual environment and install all python dependencies, run:\n160 | ```bash\n161 | # From project root\n162 | npm run backend:install\n163 | \n164 | # Or from backend directory\n165 | cd backend\n166 | python3 -m venv venv\n167 | source venv/bin/activate\n168 | pip install -r requirements.txt\n169 | ```\n170 | \n171 | #### 2. Seed Database\n172 | To seed the database with multi-tenant workspace credentials, projects, operations, invoices, support tickets, and compliance logs:\n173 | ```bash\n174 | # From project root\n175 | npm run backend:seed\n176 | \n177 | # Or from backend directory with active virtual environment\n178 | cd backend\n179 | python app/seed.py\n180 | ```","success":true}],"durationMs":2}}
