{"ts":"2026-06-27T23:00:15.848Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Infrastructure Deployment**\n\nI've confirmed the initial file creation was successful. I'm now focusing on section 2, \"Production AWS Cloud Infrastructure,\" and reviewing its content, specifically the transition to a production environment using AWS. The backend's design for AWS is the current focus of my analysis.\n\n\n**Defining Serverless Topology**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the specifics of the proposed AWS infrastructure. The plan is a cloud-native, serverless topology: FastAPI, running on AWS Lambda or ECS, interacting with DynamoDB and S3. My focus is now the DynamoDB data model, specifically the single-table design for workspace items, and I am reviewing it in depth now, considering the three tables (`GFF_USERS`, `GFF_CLIENTS`, `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`) and their keys.\n\n\n**Examining Data Models**\n\nI'm now diving deeper into the single-table DynamoDB design, specifically the data modeling for various workspace items. I'm scrutinizing the Primary Keys (`PK`), Sort Keys (`SK`), and Global Secondary Indexes (GSI) for Telemetry, Documents Metadata, Invoices/Billing, Support Tickets, and Governance/Controls. The structured keys and their relationships are under review. I've also noted that secure object storage is to be maintained using S3, and that the bucket will be named `gff-portal-documents-prod`, with block-all-public-access, server-side encryption, and strict TLS 1.3 transport.\n\n\n**Evaluating Pre-Signed URLs**\n\nI am now assessing the frontend's file interactions, which utilize dynamically generated, 15-minute Pre-signed URLs for secure access. These URLs are created via the FastAPI backend leveraging the AWS SDK (Boto3). This approach's efficiency and security are what I am considering now.\n\n\n**Reviewing Single-Table Schema**\n\nI'm now focusing on the three-table DynamoDB structure. I'm taking a close look at `GFF_USERS`, `GFF_CLIENTS`, and especially `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`, to understand how the tables fit into the high-performance single-table design for workspace items. I'm focusing on the single-table entity schema mappings for projects and AI operations, including partition keys, sort keys, and global secondary indices.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T23:00:15.850Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"qhocw2hl","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md","old_text":"and Compliance Governance Controls.","new_text":"and Compliance Governance Controls.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Production AWS Cloud Infrastructure\n\nTo transition from local SQLite development to production, the backend is engineered for a cloud-native AWS serverless topology (FastAPI on AWS Lambda/ECS connected to DynamoDB and S3).\n\n### 2.1. DynamoDB Data Modeling (Exactly 3 Tables)\nComplex relational mappings are collapsed into a high-performance single-table design for operational workspace items (`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`), alongside dedicated identity tables.\n\n| Table Name | Partition Key (PK) | Sort Key (SK) | Global Secondary Index (GSI) | Purpose |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **`GFF_USERS`** | `email` (String) | *None* | *None* | Global user credentials, roles, and client ties. |\n| **`GFF_CLIENTS`** | `client_id` (String) | *None* | *None* | Enterprise customer entity directory. |\n| **`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`** | `PK` (String) | `SK` (String) | `GSI1` (`GSI1PK` & `GSI1SK`) | Multi-tenant single-table workspace store. |\n\n#### Single-Table Entity Schema mappings (`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`)\n1. **Projects**:\n   * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>`\n   * **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `METADATA`\n2. **AI Operations (Telemetry)**:\n   * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `AIOPS#<ops_id>`\n   * **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `AIOPS#<ops_id>`\n3. **Documents Metadata**:\n   * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `DOC#<doc_id>`\n   * **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `DOC#<doc_id>`\n4. **Invoices / Billing**:\n   * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `INV#<invoice_id>`\n   * **`GSI1PK`**: `BILLING_PERIOD#<year_month>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `INV#<invoice_id>`\n5. **Support Tickets**:\n   * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `TICKET#<ticket_id>`\n   * **`GSI1PK`**: `STATUS#<status_code>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `TICKET#<ticket_id>`\n6. **Governance / Controls**:\n   * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `GOV#<gov_id>`\n   * **`GSI1PK`**: `STANDARD#<compliance_standard>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `GOV#<gov_id>`\n\n### 2.2. Secure Object Storage (Amazon S3)\n*   **Bucket Name**: `gff-portal-documents-prod`\n*   **Access Paradigm**: Block All Public Access. Enforces Server-Side Encryption (SSE-KMS) and strict TLS 1.3 transport.\n*   **Operation**: The frontend interacts with files using short-lived (15-minute) secure Pre-signed URLs dynamically generated by the FastAPI backend using AWS SDK (Boto3)."}}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T23:00:15.852Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"qhocw2hl","output":{"query":"edit:/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md","result":"Edited /Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md\n```diff\n+30: ---\n+31: \n+32: ## 2. Production AWS Cloud Infrastructure\n+33: \n+34: To transition from local SQLite development to production, the backend is engineered for a cloud-native AWS serverless topology (FastAPI on AWS Lambda/ECS connected to DynamoDB and S3).\n+35: \n+36: ### 2.1. DynamoDB Data Modeling (Exactly 3 Tables)\n+37: Complex relational mappings are collapsed into a high-performance single-table design for operational workspace items (`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`), alongside dedicated identity tables.\n+38: \n+39: | Table Name | Partition Key (PK) | Sort Key (SK) | Global Secondary Index (GSI) | Purpose |\n+40: | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n+41: | **`GFF_USERS`** | `email` (String) | *None* | *None* | Global user credentials, roles, and client ties. |\n+42: | **`GFF_CLIENTS`** | `client_id` (String) | *None* | *None* | Enterprise customer entity directory. |\n+43: | **`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`** | `PK` (String) | `SK` (String) | `GSI1` (`GSI1PK` & `GSI1SK`) | Multi-tenant single-table workspace store. |\n+44: \n+45: #### Single-Table Entity Schema mappings (`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`)\n+46: 1. **Projects**:\n+47:    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>`\n+48:    * **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `METADATA`\n+49: 2. **AI Operations (Telemetry)**:\n+50:    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `AIOPS#<ops_id>`\n+51:    * **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `AIOPS#<ops_id>`\n+52: 3. **Documents Metadata**:\n+53:    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `DOC#<doc_id>`\n+54:    * **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `DOC#<doc_id>`\n+55: 4. **Invoices / Billing**:\n+56:    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `INV#<invoice_id>`\n+57:    * **`GSI1PK`**: `BILLING_PERIOD#<year_month>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `INV#<invoice_id>`\n+58: 5. **Support Tickets**:\n+59:    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `TICKET#<ticket_id>`\n+60:    * **`GSI1PK`**: `STATUS#<status_code>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `TICKET#<ticket_id>`\n+61: 6. **Governance / Controls**:\n+62:    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `GOV#<gov_id>`\n+63:    * **`GSI1PK`**: `STANDARD#<compliance_standard>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `GOV#<gov_id>`\n+64: \n+65: ### 2.2. Secure Object Storage (Amazon S3)\n+66: *   **Bucket Name**: `gff-portal-documents-prod`\n+67: *   **Access Paradigm**: Block All Public Access. Enforces Server-Side Encryption (SSE-KMS) and strict TLS 1.3 transport.\n+68: *   **Operation**: The frontend interacts with files using short-lived (15-minute) secure Pre-signed URLs dynamically generated by the FastAPI backend using AWS SDK (Boto3).\n+69: \n```","success":true},"durationMs":2}}
