ns, and frontend base URL. I am also detailing the essential AWS configurations for deployment, including access keys and DynamoDB and S3 table names. I will use these parameters to build the API title metadata and the target regions.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T23:00:30.629Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"2mhiydp5","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md","old_text":"generated by the FastAPI backend using AWS SDK (Boto3).","new_text":"generated by the FastAPI backend using AWS SDK (Boto3).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Deployment & Operational Environment Variables\n\n### 3.1. Next.js Frontend Keys (`.env` or `.env.production`)\nSet these environment variables in your Vercel Dashboard, AWS Amplify Console, or CI/CD Pipeline:\n\n| Variable Name | Value / Format | Purpose |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` | `https://api.gff.ai/v1` | URL pointing to the FastAPI Gateway/Lambda |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV` | `production` | Deployment stage / environment tag |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_UPLOADS_ENABLED` | `true` | Enables upload features on Client Portal |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_S3_BUCKET_NAME` | `gff-portal-documents-prod` | Target S3 bucket name |\n\n### 3.2. FastAPI Backend Keys (`backend/.env` or Parameter Store / Secrets Manager)\nConfigure these environment variables inside your hosting container or AWS Lambda:\n\n| Variable Name | Value / Format | Purpose |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| `PROJECT_NAME` | `\"GFF AI Enterprise Cloud Engine\"` | API title metadata |\n| `API_V1_STR` | `\"/api/v1\"` | API prefix path |\n| `ENVIRONMENT` | `\"production\"` | Set runtime stage |\n| `CORS_ORIGINS` | `https://portal.gff.ai,https://admin.gff.ai` | Allowed frontend domains (CORS compliance) |\n| `FRONTEND_BASE_URL` | `https://portal.gff.ai` | Root URL of client-facing portal |\n| `AWS_REGION` | `us-east-1` (or chosen region) | Target region for DynamoDB and S3 |\n| `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` | *production_aws_access_key_id* | AWS IAM deployer credentials |\n| `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` | *production_aws_secret_access_key* | AWS IAM deployer secret |\n| `DYNAMODB_USERS_TABLE` | `GFF_USERS` | DynamoDB user registry table |\n| `DYNAMODB_CLIENTS_TABLE` | `GFF_CLIENTS` | DynamoDB enterprise client registry table |\n| `DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TABLE` | `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS` | Multi-tenant operational records store |\n| `DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TYPE_INDEX` | `GSI1` | Global Secondary Index for single-table queries |\n| `S3_DOCUMENTS_BUCKET` | `gff-portal-documents-prod` | Secure client document storage |\n| `S3_DOCUMENTS_PREFIX` | `clients` | File key namespace prefix |\n| `JWT_SECRET` | *cryptographically_secure_256_bit_signature_key* | Cryptographic token signing secret |\n| `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES` | `1440` (24 hours) | Token lifespan limit |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Seeded MVP Credentials\n\nThe database contains exactly **four** seeded user accounts covering the three standard RBAC roles (`gff_admin`, `client_admin`, `client_member`).\n\n| Role | Email | Password | Associated Client Tenant | Platform Clearance |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **`gff_admin`** | `gff_admin@gff.ai` | `password123` | *None* (Global) | Accesses the Admin Dashboard (`/admin/dashboard`). |\n| **`client_admin`** | `client_admin@apex.com` | `password123` | `Apex Global Solutions` (ID: 1) | Admin for Tenant 1. Full view/edit of Client Workspace. |\n| **`client_member`** | `client_member@apex.com` | `password123` | `Apex Global Solutions` (ID: 1) | Standard user for Tenant 1. Operational-only workspace rights. |\n| **`client_member`** | `client@chevron.com` | `chevron_secure_pass_2026` | `Sovereign Logistics Corp` (ID: 2) | Standard user for Tenant 2. Used to test cross-tenant data isolation. |"}}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T23:00:30.631Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"2mhiydp5","output":{"query":"edit:/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md","result":"Edited /Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md\n```diff\n+70: ---\n+71: \n+72: ## 3. Deployment & Operational Environment Variables\n+73: \n+74: ### 3.1. Next.js Frontend Keys (`.env` or `.env.production`)\n+75: Set these environment variables in your Vercel Dashboard, AWS Amplify Console, or CI/CD Pipeline:\n+76: \n+77: | Variable Name | Value / Format | Purpose |\n+78: | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n+79: | `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` | `https://api.gff.ai/v1` | URL pointing to the FastAPI Gateway/Lambda |\n+80: | `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV` | `production` | Deployment stage / environment tag |\n+81: | `NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_UPLOADS_ENABLED` | `true` | Enables upload features on Client Portal |\n+82: | `NEXT_PUBLIC_S3_BUCKET_NAME` | `gff-portal-documents-prod` | Target S3 bucket name |\n+83: \n+84: ### 3.2. FastAPI Backend Keys (`backend/.env` or Parameter Store / Secrets Manager)\n+85: Configure these environment variables inside your hosting container or AWS Lambda:\n+86: \n+87: | Variable Name | Value / Format | Purpose |\n+88: | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n+89: | `PROJECT_NAME` | `\"GFF AI Enterprise Cloud Engine\"` | API title metadata |\n+90: | `API_V1_STR` | `\"/api/v1\"` | API prefix path |\n+91: | `ENVIRONMENT` | `\"production\"` | Set runtime stage |\n+92: | `CORS_ORIGINS` | `https://portal.gff.ai,https://admin.gff.ai` | Allowed frontend domains (CORS compliance) |\n+93: | `FRONTEND_BASE_URL` | `https://portal.gff.ai` | Root URL of client-facing portal |\n+94: | `AWS_REGION` | `us-east-1` (or chosen region) | Target region for DynamoDB and S3 |\n+95: | `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` | *production_aws_access_key_id* | AWS IAM deployer credentials |\n+96: | `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` | *production_aws_secret_access_key* | AWS IAM deployer secret |\n+97: | `DYNAMODB_USERS_TABLE` | `GFF_USERS` | DynamoDB user registry table |\n+98: | `DYNAMODB_CLIENTS_TABLE` | `GFF_CLIENTS` | DynamoDB enterprise client registry table |\n+99: | `DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TABLE` | `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS` | Multi-tenant operational records store |\n+100: | `DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TYPE_INDEX` | `GSI1` | Global Secondary Index for single-table queries |\n+101: | `S3_DOCUMENTS_BUCKET` | `gff-portal-documents-prod` | Secure client document storage |\n+102: | `S3_DOCUMENTS_PREFIX` | `clients` | File key namespace prefix |\n+103: | `JWT_SECRET` | *cryptographically_secure_256_bit_signature_key* | Cryptographic token signing secret |\n+104: | `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES` | `1440` (24 hours) | Token lifespan limit |\n+105: \n+106: ---\n+107: \n+108: ## 4. Seeded MVP Credentials\n+109: \n+110: The database contains exactly **four** seeded user accounts covering the three standard RBAC roles (`gff_admin`, `client_admin`, `client_member`).\n+111: \n+112: | Role | Email | Password | Associated Client Tenant | Platform Clearance |\n+113: | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n+114: | **`gff_admin`** | `gff_admin@gff.ai` | `password123` | *None* (Global) | Accesses the Admin Dashboard (`/admin/dashboard`). |\n+115: | **`client_admin`** | `client_admin@apex.com` | `password123` | `Apex Global Solutions` (ID: 1) | Admin for Tenant 1. Full view/edit of Client Workspace. |\n+116: | **`client_member`** | `client_member@apex.com` | `password123` | `Apex Global Solutions` (ID: 1) | Standard user for Tenant 1. Operational-only workspace rights. |\n+117: | **`client_member`** | `client@chevron.com` | `chevron_secure_pass_2026` | `Sovereign Logistics Corp` (ID: 2) | Standard user for Tenant 2. Used to test cross-tenant data isolation. |\n+118: \n```","success":true},"durationMs":1}}
