{"ts":"2026-06-27T23:00:38.769Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Adding Execution Section**\n\nI'm now incorporating the \"Execution & Build Commands Reference\" section, specifically the local sandbox environment commands. This is a critical piece, and I'm ensuring it's clearly defined for immediate use.\n\n\n**Defining Production Deployment**\n\nI've transitioned to detailing production deployment. I've outlined Next.js frontend build and startup commands. I'm clarifying FastAPI's production launch, specifying Uvicorn worker configuration for multi-threaded deployment. I'm focusing on providing practical, direct commands.\n\n\n**Specifying AWS Lambda Route**\n\nI'm now detailing the API Gateway setup. The focus is routing traffic to a Lambda function housing the FastAPI app, using `Mangum` for ASGI adaptation.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T23:00:38.771Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"aj2sc8ts","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md","old_text":"| **`client_member`** | `client@chevron.com` | `chevron_secure_pass_2026` | `Sovereign Logistics Corp` (ID: 2) | Standard user for Tenant 2. Used to test cross-tenant data isolation. |","new_text":"| **`client_member`** | `client@chevron.com` | `chevron_secure_pass_2026` | `Sovereign Logistics Corp` (ID: 2) | Standard user for Tenant 2. Used to test cross-tenant data isolation. |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Execution & Build Commands Reference\n\n### 5.1. Local Sandbox Environment Execution\nRun these commands from the root of the workspace during local development:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Install Backend Dependencies (FastAPI, SQLite, SQLite-Utils, Pytest)\nnpm run backend:install\n\n# 2. Setup SQLite Schema & Inject Multi-Tenant Seed Users/Items\nnpm run backend:seed\n\n# 3. Launch Local Hot-Reloading FastAPI Backend (Standard Port: 8000)\nnpm run backend:dev\n\n# 4. Launch Local Hot-Reloading Next.js Frontend (Standard Port: 3000)\nnpm run dev\n\n# 5. Run Security, RBAC & End-to-End API Integration Smoke Tests\nnpm run backend:check\n```\n\n### 5.2. Production Deployment Execution\nPrepare and run production workloads with these instructions:\n\n#### Next.js Frontend Production Build\nTo create an optimized production bundle and boot the production web server locally or in a container:\n```bash\n# Build the application\nnpm run build\n\n# Start the node runtime production server\nnpm run start\n```\n\n#### FastAPI Backend Production Launch\nTo boot the FastAPI server using multi-threaded Uvicorn workers in cloud hosting VMs, containers, or on-premises servers:\n```bash\n# Production launch command (4 workers, host bound to all network interfaces)\nuvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --workers 4\n```\n*(For Serverless AWS Lambda deployments, configure API Gateway to route to a Lambda containing the FastAPI application wrapped with the `Mangum` ASGI adapter).*"}}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T23:00:38.772Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"aj2sc8ts","output":{"query":"edit:/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md","result":"Edited /Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md\n```diff\n+119: ---\n+120: \n+121: ## 5. Execution & Build Commands Reference\n+122: \n+123: ### 5.1. Local Sandbox Environment Execution\n+124: Run these commands from the root of the workspace during local development:\n+125: \n+126: ```bash\n+127: # 1. Install Backend Dependencies (FastAPI, SQLite, SQLite-Utils, Pytest)\n+128: npm run backend:install\n+129: \n+130: # 2. Setup SQLite Schema & Inject Multi-Tenant Seed Users/Items\n+131: npm run backend:seed\n+132: \n+133: # 3. Launch Local Hot-Reloading FastAPI Backend (Standard Port: 8000)\n+134: npm run backend:dev\n+135: \n+136: # 4. Launch Local Hot-Reloading Next.js Frontend (Standard Port: 3000)\n+137: npm run dev\n+138: \n+139: # 5. Run Security, RBAC & End-to-End API Integration Smoke Tests\n+140: npm run backend:check\n+141: ```\n+142: \n+143: ### 5.2. Production Deployment Execution\n+144: Prepare and run production workloads with these instructions:\n+145: \n+146: #### Next.js Frontend Production Build\n+147: To create an optimized production bundle and boot the production web server locally or in a container:\n+148: ```bash\n+149: # Build the application\n+150: npm run build\n+151: \n+152: # Start the node runtime production server\n+153: npm run start\n+154: ```\n+155: \n+156: #### FastAPI Backend Production Launch\n+157: To boot the FastAPI server using multi-threaded Uvicorn workers in cloud hosting VMs, containers, or on-premises servers:\n+158: ```bash\n+159: # Production launch command (4 workers, host bound to all network interfaces)\n+160: uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --workers 4\n+161: ```\n+162: *(For Serverless AWS Lambda deployments, configure API Gateway to route to a Lambda containing the FastAPI application wrapped with the `Mangum` ASGI adapter).*\n+163: \n```","success":true},"durationMs":1}}
